@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
@TOC "MAIN"

Intoduction:
АААААААААААА

I think you already know what PsPrt is, so you already know how usefull it
is.
The only problem I had using it was the not so very handy way to configure
it, so I wrote MUIPsPrt.

PS: if you don't like MUI, simply delete MUIPsPrt from your HD..

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installing" "Installing MUIPsPrt"
@TOC "MAIN"

Installing MUIPsPrt:
АААААААААААААААААААА

Very easy: simply copy it where you have place on your HD ;-)
The preference file for PsPrt (psprt.prefs) is stored in Env: and EnvArc:

@ENDNODE

@NODE "GUI" "Connecting an IOMEGA ZIP drive to your AMIGA"
@TOC "MAIN"

The GUI interface:
АААААААААААААААААА

I think that MUIPsPrt is very easy to use, and if you have any problem
there is an online help (thanks to MUI;-).

If you don't understand what on option means, simply read the PsPrt manual!

I added the option to print a PS file directly from MUIPsPrt, so you don't
have to mount the PsPrt:  device and then copy the file to it, MUIPsPrt
will do it automagically for you..
The first time you print something, it's possible that you get a "Please
Insert PSPRT:  disk" error message:  simply select cancel and the PSPRT:
device will be mounted automatically.

@ENDNODE

